Anyways… welcome, rookie. From now on, I am your venerated boss in this marvelous store.
Your duty? Charge customers properly. Simple enough, right?
Since I don’t want to fry your tiny brain on your very first day, we’ll just focus on two directions: up and right.
To your right, you’ll see a cash register. That’s where the money your customer brought will appear.
Further right, you’ll find a table with the standard prices of all the products we sell here.
Now look up. You’ll see two chains, each with its own specific use. Pay attention!
If it’s a rope with green mold, you pull that when the customer’s payment is all correct.
If it’s a red-grip chain, you pull that when something doesn’t add up.
Charge correctly? You get a shiny coin. Mess up? Forget about your tips.
Speaking of tips — they’re in the jar to your left. But I’d rather not point you in another direction today.
I doubt my insurance covers what happens if your brain overheats.

Ah… I hope you’re a commoner who at least knows how to charge things.

And you… well… you do what you can, I suppose.
Hmph. I suppose even someone like you can get it right sometimes.
Another reason nobility should never mingle with your kind.
Ciao, fratello.

Got the recipe from a charming little book — like the Necronomicon but… tastier.
I need this beer as an ingredient… or anesthetic, not sure yet.
And the cat bones? For the broth, obviously.

Coupon not valid?! That’s one recipe gone to hell.

Have you considered joining our church?

Good luck with the shop, human.
FAST! I NEED TO REFUEL!

Prepping for the 500 Spin Cycle Grand Prix!
I’ve got a spoiler on my back and wheels on my shoes!

Poor kid’s gonna learn real quick how sad and rough life is.

Now my kid will see me even sadder than usual…

Do any of the following seem tied to that cult?

Morning, human.
How’s life in my mother’s basement? Comfy? Cozy? Damp and full of trauma?
Don’t answer. I don’t care.
Made friends with the rats yet? Careful— One of them is called Smirky and he’s on payroll.

En fin… ¡A currar!
Hey, little one!
My gnome is still lost somewhere in the shop.

Good luck, shorty.

Stupid human. Luckily my slime workers will be smarter than you.
Hey buddy, got bad news for you…

Painful way to end things… though not worse than when an ex left me for my brother.

Now that I’m a real limbastic, maybe I can start over.
Starting with getting back to work— I’ve been on shift for three hours already.
I’m kicking off my new retirement into loneliness with enthusiasm.
I hope my new path doesn’t get derailed by my non-existent coin-counting skills.
Hello h-human, how be your day?
Like you s-s-see… I b-broke runes again.
I was at bar last night with my dear family…
Until a drunk spilled drink on me— all drink!
They broke more during night.
My runes no talk well anymore… charge me, want to change them now.
Thank you human, change runes no time.
I no can talk, I no break rule.
Hey, hey, hey! It’s me again: PATXI!!!
But this time I’m not here for work… well, okay, a little.
I’m here for love..! Love with glasses, specifically.

Alright, charme me A.S.A.P!

WHAT?! He really needs these potions!

They went right back to being inferior again.
Do you have those memories too? Oh right… you’re young.

Oh… that’s how my second crisis started after my husband left me.

Terry and I were hired as official entertainers!

Whileee... I did the Battle Mambo remix.

Best part was the Blood of my enemies Punch and it's ice statue. A true work of art.

Thanks, bro! I’ll get you a ticket for the next geriatric breakdance battle for sure!
Ugh… now I can’t avenge myself on the lady who threw the cane at me >:T
HELLO, BUDDY! Ready for the next big party?

How FUN!!!

YOU’RE THE BESTTTTT! See you at the next retirees’ rave!
WHAAAT?! How am I gonna pull off my magic trick now?

I should go to Muscle Beluga, best gym in the kingdom, to get ripped.

The customers get worse every day… T-they never respect th-the rules..!

S-s-sorry if I’m talking too much… charge me, there’s probably a line.
Th-thanks, I hope my dad likes these human-shaped plushies.
S-sorry, I didn’t know the coupon was f-fake!

A gigantic hill… at least a meter and a half tall.
I climbed to the top and found a frog-faced rock.
Then I slipped, rolled all the way down, and discovered a new species: the “Rock-Hopper.”
It stung me in one ear, but I survived.
I still need some items to really survive though, so i'll take these to, literally not die.
Thanks, human! I’ll bring you something from my next expedition if I remember!
Ohh… you left me frozen… I...
Well, well—my favorite human, looking more radiant every day.
Is it the heat of the shop, or does my lava rise when you look at me?
I went to erupt at the spa yesterday, but they said I was too explosive.

Subtlety isn’t your strength, huh?
Would you… uh… like to help adjust my thermal valves one night?
Heh… kidding! Unless I’m not.

Mghmm… if only you knew how good you charge… makes me want to buy here even more.

Tomorrow I’ll review what you did wrong, so… rest up.
Mid night, human. Tomorrow will be a hard day...
Hello, last day human! Did you know today is special?

Nice, bro. I’d trust you with my favorite picante mix.

Mamma mia! Bad omens already!

When we revive the heroes, I hope you know I’ll remember this.
Sup… damn hybrid rules!

Why can’t a toad-hippo live his liiiife, huh?

Starting off with debts already… just like the good old days!
Hey, cutie… I got fired…

Anyway, I don’t think I’ll need my adventure gear anymore.
As a keepsake, you can have this map.

Greetings from an existence… slightly less somber.

I no longer cast sad looks… now they’re just intense.
Ring these up, they’re for his graduation from dark kindergarten.
Thank you… feels nice to gift something that isn’t melancholy.
Well… just another embroidered shadow.
Hello, darling…

Ring me up—I’m starting to feel unwell.

Great, I don’t even know where my head is.
Hi plain outfit hum- ough, that reminds me that i was used as a coat rack at the museum… AGAIN!

Beer to lubricate the kneecaps, mana in case I fall apart mid-step.

Never worthy of me...
Will this shop ever be-

I’ll buy some delicacies—I want to celebrate my future victory in the Inherited Magic Tournament.

HOW DARE YOU?!

If I died programming and I’m still programming dead… did I ever live?

I started writing a book: 404: Life Meaning Not Found.
Well, let's get this over with! I need to keep writing.
Th-thanks… the code compiled quickly today.
Uh… not sure what I did wrong this time.

Thanks to my sweetheart I feel much better.
Ring me up—I want to buy him a gift.
Th-thanks… keep my glasses, I don’t need them anymore.

Tonight, we’ll raid their temple and arrest as many cult members as we can.

Who hit the victim with the orb?
